@page "/cookie-policy"

<PageTitle>Cookie Policy — PDFToolstack</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Cookie Policy for PdfToolStack, including essential cookies, preference cookies, analytics, advertising settings, and cookie controls." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://pdftoolstack.com/cookie-policy" />
</HeadContent>

<div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-container">

        <div class="legal-header">
            <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
            <p class="legal-date">Effective date: May 20, 2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="legal-content">

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>1. What Are Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    Cookies are small text files that are placed
                    on your device when you visit a website. They
                    are widely used to make websites work more
                    efficiently and to provide information to
                    website owners.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    PDFToolstack uses cookies for the following
                    purposes:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Essential cookies</strong> —
                        These are necessary for the website to
                        function and cannot be switched off. They
                        are usually set in response to actions
                        you take such as setting your privacy
                        preferences or filling in forms.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Preference cookies</strong> —
                        These allow us to remember choices you
                        make such as your selected color theme,
                        so we can provide a more personalized
                        experience.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Analytics cookies</strong> —
                        These help us understand how visitors
                        interact with our website by collecting
                        and reporting information
                        anonymously.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Advertising cookies</strong> —
                        These may be used if advertising features
                        are enabled on the site. PdfToolStack does
                        not require advertising cookies for core
                        PDF processing tools.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>3. Cookies We Use</h2>
                <table class="cookie-table">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Cookie Name</th>
                            <th>Purpose</th>
                            <th>Duration</th>
                            <th>Type</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td>pdftoolstack-theme</td>
                            <td>Stores your selected color theme</td>
                            <td>1 year</td>
                            <td>Preference</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>_ga</td>
                            <td>Google Analytics — tracks sessions</td>
                            <td>2 years</td>
                            <td>Analytics</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>_gid</td>
                            <td>Google Analytics — tracks users</td>
                            <td>24 hours</td>
                            <td>Analytics</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Ad provider cookies</td>
                            <td>Used for ad delivery or measurement only if advertising is enabled</td>
                            <td>Varies by provider and browser settings</td>
                            <td>Advertising</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>4. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    We may use Google Analytics and, if advertising
                    is enabled, Google AdSense. These services may
                    set their own cookies on your device. Third-party
                    cookies are governed by the provider's privacy
                    policy. You
                    can learn more at
                    <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                       target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                        Google Privacy Policy
                    </a>.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>5. Managing Cookies</h2>
                <p>
                    You can control and manage cookies in several
                    ways:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Browser settings</strong> — Most
                        browsers allow you to refuse or delete
                        cookies through their settings
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Google opt-out</strong> — Visit
                        <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads"
                           target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                            Google Ad Settings
                        </a> to opt out of
                        personalized advertising
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Our cookie banner</strong> — Use
                        the cookie preferences banner when you
                        first visit our site
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    Please note that disabling certain cookies
                    may affect the functionality of our
                    website.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="legal-section">
                <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>
                    If you have questions about our use of
                    cookies, please contact us at
                    <a href="mailto:admin@pdftoolstack.com">
                        admin@pdftoolstack.com
                    </a>.
                </p>
            </section>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
